from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score

# Assuming X, y, and test_size are defined from previous steps
X_train, X_cv, y_train, y_cv = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3) 

# Rectified Model Initialization
# Removed multi_class, n_jobs, and set class_weight to None (object)
model = LogisticRegression(
    C=1.0, 
    class_weight=None, 
    dual=False, 
    fit_intercept=True, 
    intercept_scaling=1, 
    penalty='l2', 
    random_state=1, 
    solver='liblinear', 
    tol=0.0001, 
    verbose=0, 
    warm_start=False
)

# Fitting the model (this line should now execute without the ValueError)
model.fit(X_train, y_train) 

# Prediction and Evaluation
pred_cv = model.predict(X_cv)
accuracy_score(y_cv, pred_cv)

from sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold
kf = StratifiedKFold(
    n_splits=5, 
    random_state=1, 
    shuffle=True
)


i = 1 
for train_index, test_index in kf.split(X, y): 
    print(f'\n *k of fold {i}*') 
   
    X_train, X_cv = X.iloc[train_index], X.iloc[test_index]
    y_train, y_cv = y.iloc[train_index], y.iloc[test_index]

    # Initialize and train the model for the current fold
    model = LogisticRegression(random_state=1) 
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)

    # Predict on the cross-validation set and the held-out test set
    pred_cv = model.predict(X_cv)
    
    # Calculate and print the accuracy score for the current fold
    score = accuracy_score(y_cv, pred_cv)
    print(f'accuracy_score: {score}')
    
    # Increment the fold counter
    i += 1 
    
    # The image shows predictions on the test set inside the loop, 
    # which is not standard practice for final submission but extracts the code as written.
    # pred_test = model.predict(test)
    
# Final prediction step shown at the end of the loop structure
pred_test = model.predict(test) # Predict on the full, held-out 'test' set with the last trained model
pred_prob = model.predict_proba(X_cv)[:, 1] # Get probability of positive class (Y=1) for CV set

# Setup Stratified K-Fold Cross-Validation

kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, random_state=1, shuffle=True)

# Loop through folds
for train_index, test_index in kf.split(X, y):
    print('\n{} of kfold {}'.format(i, kf.n_splits))
    
    # Split data for the current fold
    xtr, xvl = X.iloc[train_index], X.iloc[test_index]
    ytr, yvl = y.iloc[train_index], y.iloc[test_index]
    
    # Initialize and train the Logistic Regression model
    model = LogisticRegression(random_state=1)
    model.fit(xtr, ytr)
    
    # Predict on validation set
   
    
    # Calculate and print accuracy for the current fold
    score = accuracy_score(yvl, pred_test)
    print('accuracy_score', score)

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold # Assuming this is needed for kf initialization

# Initialize Stratified K-Fold
kf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, random_state=1, shuffle=True)

# Initialize fold counter
i = 1

# Loop through folds for cross-validation
for train_index, test_index in kf.split(X, y):
    print('\n{} of kfold {}'.format(i, kf.n_splits))
    
    # Split data for the current fold
    # Note: .loc is used for slicing based on index labels
    xtr, xvl = X.loc[train_index], X.loc[test_index] 
    ytr, yvl = y.loc[train_index], y.loc[test_index]
    
    # Initialize and train the Decision Tree Classifier model
    model = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=1)
    model.fit(xtr, ytr)
    
    # Calculate and print accuracy for the current fold
    score = accuracy_score(yvl, pred_test) # Assuming accuracy_score is imported
    print('accuracy_score', score)
